05/02/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Five donor countries -- Great Britain, the Netherlands, Norway, Spain and Sweden -- will provide around 11m euros in financial assistance to the BiH courts and prosecutors, according to the BiH Justice Ministry.
It announced on Friday (February 2nd) that representatives of the government and the states had sealed a memorandum to that effect.
The funding will be earmarked for units prosecuting war crimes, organised crime, economic crime and corruption.
(PBS BiH, RTRS, Srna - 02/02/07)
